The paper proposes a method for Neural Architecture Search (NAS) which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) research. The method involves model pruning and optimization, which are common techniques in deep learning (DL) and ML. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization and regularization techniques, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves neural networks, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
